{
  "stem": "19198.1",
  "chunk_idx": 4,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 8.3,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "So I was fairly close to them, but that was strictly a Shabbat friendship.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "The rest of the time I spent with young people my own age, none of whom was Jewish.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Yes.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Oh, absolutely.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Not-- not until the Nazis actually took over.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Now, the-- if you would have asked the question, when did I become aware of anti-Semitism, that was very early.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "I specifically remember one incident when I probably was no more than five or six years old when I was walking in one direction on a street on the sidewalk.",
      "word_count": 30
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "A youngster who lived a few doors away from my grandparents walked in the opposite direction on the other side.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "He didn't pay attention to where he was going.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "He stumbled, fell, got up, and then shook his fist at me and says, you damn Jew.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "Now, that th the first actual event of anti-Jewish feeling that I witnessed, even though I was very much aware of the fact that as Jews we were different and there were people who didn't like Jews.",
      "word_count": 37
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Well, the feeling that I was different was from the very fact that I went to synagogue and everybody else went to the church.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "The-- there was no secret of our being Jews.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "We were not terribly self-conscious about our being Jews, but we were conscious of the fact that has Jews we were different from people who were not Jews.",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Yes.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "I told my parents and they said, well, they-- they did not-- were not aware that that family was in any way anti-Semitic and we continued to have a very good relationship with these neighbors.",
      "word_count": 35
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "But somehow, this boy had picked up the idea somewhere.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "It was there.",
      "word_count": 3
    }
  ],
